# Test Case Generator Spec

## Overview
AI-powered test case generation tool that converts user stories, requirements, or feature descriptions into comprehensive test cases with multiple scenarios.

## Requirements

### Functional Requirements
- Accept user input (user story, feature description, or requirements)
- Generate test cases using AI (Gemini API)
- Support multiple test case types: Functional, Edge Cases, Negative, Performance
- Display generated test cases in organized format
- Allow editing of generated test cases
- Save test cases to library
- Export test cases (JSON, CSV)
- Copy individual test cases to clipboard

### UI Requirements
- Clean, modern interface with dark theme
- Textarea for input with placeholder guidance
- Generate button with loading state
- Tabbed interface for different test case types
- Card-based layout for test cases
- Action buttons: Edit, Save to Library, Copy, Export

### Technical Requirements
- React functional components with hooks
- Integration with Gemini API via backend
- Context API for state management
- Supabase for data persistence
- Toast notifications for user feedback

## Implementation

### Components
- `TestCaseGenerator.jsx` - Main page component
- Uses `useApp` context for state management
- Uses `apiService` for AI generation
- Uses `supabaseService` for data persistence

### API Integration
```javascript
POST /api/generate-test-cases
Body: { input: string, type: string }
Response: { testCases: Array }
```

### Data Structure
```javascript
{
  id: string,
  title: string,
  description: string,
  preconditions: string,
  steps: Array<string>,
  expectedResult: string,
  priority: string,
  type: string,
  createdAt: timestamp
}
```

## User Flow
1. User enters feature description or user story
2. User clicks "Generate Test Cases"
3. AI processes input and generates test cases
4. Test cases displayed in tabs (Functional, Edge Cases, etc.)
5. User can edit, save, or export test cases
6. Saved test cases appear in Library

## Success Criteria
- Generate relevant test cases within 5 seconds
- Support various input formats
- Generate minimum 3-5 test cases per category
- 95% user satisfaction with generated quality
- Zero data loss on save operations
